<p>In counseling, we make our thoughts, behaviors, and moods the subject of close examination. At the heart of this process is the <em>compassionate interview</em> — a unique dialogue in which individuals are free to safely examine the resistances that keeps them feeling stuck.</p>

<p>I offer talk therapy to individuals who have received a psychiatric diagnosis and are responding to a significant incident in life. My clients are often facing high conflict divorce, legal issues or financial crisis often driven by problematic behaviors.</p>

